<subSubSection id="C328ABCEFFA448157BB0FC4EFE0A4B6D" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFA448157BB0FC4EFE954CA0" blockId="25.[189,310,926,952]" box="[189,310,926,952]" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">
<heading id="D0C54F29FFA448157BB0FC4EFE954CA0" bold="true" box="[189,310,926,952]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA448157BB0FC4EFE954CA0" bold="true" box="[189,310,926,952]" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFA448157BB0FC1EFE0A4B6D" blockId="25.[188,1399,973,1141]" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">
It shares the presence of incomplete notauli with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA4481579F9FC1EFC244CFF" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[756,903,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atricornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA4481579F9FC1EFC244CFF" box="[756,903,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">A. atricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA448157898FC1EFBE44CFF" box="[917,1095,973,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA448157898FC1EFBE44CFF" box="[917,1095,973,1000]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">A. flavidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA448157F88FC1EFB5C4CFF" box="[1157,1279,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA448157F88FC1EFB584CFF" authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1951" box="[1157,1275,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paucus">A. paucus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, it can be easily distinguished due to the absence of mesoscutal and scutellar sculpture (other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA448157BB0FBC3FEBE4B35" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" box="[189,285,1043,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA448157BB0FBC3FEBE4B35" box="[189,285,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">Aegilips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
present some degree of sculpture in the scutellum) and the presence an elongated 2rm vein, a character that sets it apart from other Palaearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA44815786AFBE7FC644B49" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" box="[871,967,1079,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA44815786AFBE7FC644B49" box="[871,967,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">Aegilips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vein 2rm absent in other Palaearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA448157A35FB8AFE3B4B6C" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" box="[312,408,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA448157A35FB8AFE3B4B6C" box="[312,408,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="133">Aegilips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
